- The number of packets transmitted (2887) and bytes transmitted (~8.6MB) is high for a typical normal flow.
- The flags indicate no FIN or RST flag was sent, suggesting an ongoing connection rather than an attempt to close it quickly, which might be seen in port scan attacks.
- Given the sustained duration (2.015 seconds) and the large number of packets transmitted, this appears more consistent with a denial-of-service attack than other types of attacks.
